President Obama was updated on the status of American service members who were wounded while attempting to evacuate American citizens in South Sudan. He directed his national security team to ensure the safety of the military personnel and to work with the United Nations to evacuate citizens from the area. He participated in a secure call with his national security advisors to further update him on the situation. The President was pleased to hear that the service members are in stable condition and emphasized the importance of working with the United Nations to secure citizens in South Sudan. He also urged South Sudan's leaders to resolve their differences through dialogue and warned that continued violence would jeopardize the progress of independence. President Obama expressed appreciation for the work of the military and civilians in South Sudan and instructed his team to keep him updated on the situation.